[A quick peek at the maps referenced in these reports (see OIE website)
shows how widespread the outbreaks are in China and Thailand. In case
anyone thinks we have the outbreaks under control in poultry in Asia, these
data should provide ample caution and resolve and should stimulate the
allocation of adequate resources. Since last week, 8 new provinces have
been affected in Thailand and 15 new outbreaks in China. Other countries,
including Laos, Cambodia, and Indonesia, which did not file OIE update
reports this week, are still experiencing new outbreaks -- see Avian
influenza - Eastern Asia (24) 20040213.0480. - Mod.PC]
